\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\ul\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 Autobiographical memory}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 Her writing about the school draws on her own autobiographical memory. Sh
irley Ardener a key influence: suggested her first article on Gipsy women, and then her first talk on her school experience \endash 
 January 1978 to Queen Elizabeth House seminar. Some women in audience very moved. Had to fight own despair in writing about these memories. This approach in anthropology supported by David Pocock, with idea of \lquote personal anthropology\rquote 
; Paul Barker sent to her to review.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 Helen Callaway agreed to co-edit conference papers on }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 Anthropology and Autobiography}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 . Had been proposed as future theme at big open meeting of previous conference. Firth and Leach supported her, Anthony Cohen against.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
