\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\ul\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 Track 3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\ul\insrsid8534382 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\ul\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 Various research and teaching jobs [1965-70]}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\ul\insrsid8534382 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 Devastated by award of 3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\super\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 rd}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382  [would now be a 2:2]. Hugh Brody given SSRC studentship despite only 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\super\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 nd}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 . Better revision teaching for men. While in Heyford, part-time job with Henri Tajfel, psychologist on group mentality. Research was on children and racism. Worked in a Headington primary school recording children
\rquote s racial attitudes. Did most of the research, but published by supervisor without JO\rquote s name.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 Second part-time job at Nu
ffield about building Cowley shopping centre. Questionnaire surveys in Cowley: valuable experience, interviewing white working class. All preset questions, except for final two inch space. Realised not enough space for people\rquote 
s personal opinions. In that era apparently some (especially male) Research assistants forging interview answers in cafes.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 JO\rquote  articles on fieldwork. Anthony Jackson insisted of publishing despite objections of reader Ralph Grillo that it was too anecdotal. JO\rquote s plan to write a campus
 novel. Young and Willmott in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 The Symmetrical Family}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382  do mention interviewers\rquote 
 names. Research assistants are like cash croppers, you provide the data, they write it up. Strength of Marsden\rquote s work that it does draw on autobiography to make sense of the material.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382 

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 Third term after graduating}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 ,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382  teaching two days a week in Catholic Secondary Modern in Banbury, the only graduate on staff. Headmaster\rquote s question and answer method. He shocked by Mr Gradgrind style seen as absurd for those who had f
ailed the 11 plus. But not put off  teaching.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 One year after degree, Hugh Brody given permanent lectureship in  Philosophy at Queen\rquote 
s Belfast. Judith commuted, now taking college teacher training certificate at Garnett College. Hugh proposed before he met women students. They had fallen out over 1967 war. He stayed only one year in Belfast, then came back to Oxford.}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 After Garnett, JO taught day release students at Banbury Tech. Discovered Hugh had another woman, relationship broke. Meanwhile she had found
 another man, Jim Hopkins, philosopher, married. Judith with him 17 years till 1984 Became manic depressive. But supported JO doing anthropology.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 Got the taste for fieldwork with Hugh, but did not then see it as anthropology. He had no other permanent jobs. Went to London and then on to write about Canadian Inuit \endash 
 so both later wrote about nomads. Mother had admired Margaret Mead. Earlier incident, Principal  forbad JO to leave Oxford overnight at weekend to hear Margaret Mead.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 Got a job as babysitter for A.L. and Jennifer Hart, brain-damaged child: given free room, but gave up because child so undisciplined. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f39\fs22\insrsid8534382 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\ul\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 Cambridge [1969-70] }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\ul\insrsid8534382 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 Jim elected fellow of King\rquote s, so JO moved to Cambridge \endash  but he only moved there later after all. 
JO took Cambridge Certificate in Anthropology. Had been rejected by Godfrey Leinhardt for Oxford because of 3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\super\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 rd}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 . Interviewed by Meyer Fortes. Edmund Leach her inspiration, two hours weekly in group of 5. Otherwise took undergraduate courses.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 Most influent
ial teachers included Stanley Tambiah, Sri Lanka, biographer of Leach, brilliant lectures. Meyer Fortes less coherent but passionate. Students included Tim Ingold and Chris Fuller at Fortes weekly seminar. Story of Fortes picking her out at a party for de
termination. Leach inspirational; got to know him personally later on. JO living and working in rented garden office.  Jack Goody chaotic lecturer, enthusiastic. At Asian seminars met John Parry. For her, Cambridge intellectually richer than Oxford.}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 Attach
ed to Newnham, but not comfortable there. Feels her accent is disliked. Recent contacts, raising funds and launching archive. Esther Goody refused to be her tutor [but much later secured publication of her book by Cambridge University Press in series of h
er husband Jack). Final terms secured CND friend Malcolm McLeod as tutor. No dissertation, less good at unseen exams. Underactive thyroid diagnosed much later [1997].}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\ul\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 Researching }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f39\fs22\ul\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 The Traveller-Gypsies}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f39\fs22\ul\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382  [1971-73]}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\ul\insrsid8534382 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 Saw advert for researcher on Gypsies and gov
ernment policy from quango, Centre for Environmental Studies, London. Dozens of applicants. Before job interview found first census of Gypsies (1968) in Oxford City Library, which impressed the interviewer who had written it. Weak reference from Brian Wil
son. But offered job, seen as hardworking and keen, but not \lquote a boffin\rquote , not dominating.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\ul\insrsid8534382 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\ul\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 Track 4}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 Appointed to research job because a social scientist, and anthropology deals with the exotic, but not for its method. Under Barbara Adams, based at Centre fo
r Environmental Studies in Regents Park. Barbara gave her pile of local reports on Gypsies. JO realised these full of stereotypes, ranking them in terms of  \lquote blood\rquote  and criminality. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f39\fs22\insrsid8534382 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 Then Barbara introduced her to Don Byrne, Herts county employee, liberal
, in spirit of 1969 Act. He had allowed temporary site near St Albans to stay open. Photo of JO and her caravan which she shows at lectures: authority of the autobiographical I, \lquote That\rquote s where I lived\rquote 
, undermines critics. Triangular patch between dual carr
iageways. Court case between councils resulted in site having a warden. Introduced, posing as a friend rather than as a researcher, by Penny Vincent, who was working for Gypsy children. Met Norman McCabe, warden, and visited other sites with Penny. Patric
k McNeill.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 
Before long Norman went on holiday, and JO moved into his caravan as deputy. Took very full hand-written  notes (which intends to donate to Newnham College, Cambridge). Later living in b & b, visiting daily. Don Byrne offered her a caravan on an
y site, but he was later upset by aspects of her later report: he assumed Gypsies would all want settlement, housing and employment, as did Barbara Adams. Difficulties when expected to collect rents, but let off this responsibility by Don.}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 Barbara asked her to compose a questionnaire, a method which JO was against. Barbara then composed a 25-page schedule, including the question, \lquote Why do you travel\rquote 
, meaningless to a nomad.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 Importance of early accidental meetings, as with Jean, whose infant had been run o
ver by careless lorry driver; would sit at night talking; gave her a detailed account of fortune telling (see chapter in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 Own and Other Culture}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 
\ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 ). Some people do welcome outsiders. The people who talked most were partly of mixed culture: had lived parts of t
heir lives in houses or were in army or from mixed parentage. The most articulate were those who had seen both sides, rather than the \lquote typical\rquote  Gypsy.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 
To avoid being identified as a researcher, JO gave questionnaire to Penny, who administered it to families she knew; but JO realised many answers lies, such as denying had been married before. Barbara decided the interviews self-contradictory, so did not 
c
ode them. JO feels quantitative method is more vulnerable to such false information. The more you generalise the more you lose detail. Barbara wanted tables, to influence government policy. Brilliant article by Leach contrasts a social survey of 52 villag
es with his own year\rquote s work in one village. The intensive study shows the overall system: e.g. that peasants now landless may be heirs to land. Inspired by Malinowski\rquote s tent in the Trobriand Islands. Pauline Lane.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 
\ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 The quantitative method is \lquote inherently authoritarian\rquote ; but what of the colonial dimension of anthropology? This argument is addressed in Tala Asad, }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 Anthropology and the Colonial Encounter}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 
. Wendy James, professor at Oxford, argued that anthropologists saw themselves as protectors of indigenous people against the colonial system. Perry Anderson\rquote 
s critique of Evans Pritchard, given access to Nuer because Colonial Office were worried about charismatic religious leaders. Similar dilemmas now for those working for NGOs. Gave lecture at LSE in honour of Obi}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\b\f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 Igwara, Nigerian colleague at Hull, but Obi\rquote s boyfriend was against JO, assuming her to be a racist.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 
\ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 Contradictions between objectives of Herts CC and JO\rquote s understanding of Gypsies. Gypsy children misunderstood as deprived, when learning through work. 
Save the Children tried to get them painting. Ministry of Housing did not want Barbara to work on Gypsies, but on housing. Insufficient sites provided under 1969 Act, but very controlling, allowing eviction from unofficial sites. Barbara sympathetic but a
ssumed Gypsies wanted integration, jobs and housing. JO saw they did not want integration, and that their culture was dynamic and resourceful. But some of them saw her as a spy.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 JO got close to them with Jean\rquote s help, her advice on clothing, not to show body. This has now changed. Dislikes stereotyping of \lquote My Gypsy Wedding\rquote 
 film. Instinctively changed pose: photo, standing next to a Gypsy, Beatrice, with same \lquote barrier pose\rquote . (Article, \lquote Fieldwork embodied\rquote .) }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 Breakthrough when on second site. Again got close to people of mixed background, such as show people. Reena}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\b\f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 ,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 
 literate, semi-separated from husband, who had lorry. JO learnt to drive, bought cheap van, with Reena began calling for scrap. Unsuccessfully trie
d to change her accent; then pretended collecting for Save the Children, until encountered their local secretary. This experience \lquote a liberation\rquote . Learn to admire their skills, and learn from your own mistakes.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 
\ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 Joined potato gang. Until 1990s Gypsies were 
responsible for most fruit-picking in England. Earlier, children allowed to miss school for harvesting. Occasion when mistaken by police for a Gypsy. Oxford neighbour anti-Gypsy.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 Sometimes helped to write letters. They could live without literacy. Ignored threatening content of eviction letters.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f39\fs22\insrsid8534382 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 Taking a pregnant woman to hospital. She was very against having twins \endash  comparison with Nuer, who drowned twins.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f39\fs22\insrsid8534382 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 Listening to bereaved, as with Jean, a form of therapy. No photos of lost children.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 No separate language. Picked up words from listening. Linguists dislike her focus on words of different derivations. People\rquote 
s practices and beliefs should not be explained just in terms of origin. \lquote Pal\rquote  a Romany word. Jane Szurek encouraged her to draw on Marxist. Fall of feudalism. The language travelled from Eastern Europe independently of people.}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 Some writers hostile because she is not Jewish: Yaron Matras has claimed that she had a \lquote self righteous crusade against Gipsy history\rquote , while others called her an 
\lquote enemy of the Romany people\rquote 
. Ian Hancock on Romany as a creole language; now megastar in Texas, has retracted earlier view, very hostile to JO. Experience of anti-semitism drives victims to anti-Gypsyism. Cambridge conference, Leach supported her idea that Gypsies
 were recruited from fall of feudalism.  JO never denied an Indian connection but contested that all Gypsies and their beliefs were Hindu and that they were all genetically from India.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 Meeting of concerned researchers (including Thomas Acton, sociologist)
 at Oxford, when JO threatened. Acton hates her accent and later confessed to someone he was jealous of the popularity of her subsequent book}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 At Centre for Environmental Studies met Michael Harloe, working on impact of Swindon New Town \endash  later on intervie
w panel for Essex job. Protest led by Doreen Massey (geographer, helping US conscripts to escape) against research funds being used to study a minority. But David Donnison, Director, got money from Rowntree for Gypsy project. JO shocked by hostility of ra
dicals, linguists. False myths that Gypsy customs come from India.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 No advice in literature then on how to write fieldnotes. Used headings \endash 
 travel, kinship, etc. Advised from Malcolm McLeod in Cambridge: write down everything you see, you hear, you smell \endash  an exercise book a day! Don\rquote t decide in advance what is relevant \endash 
 unlike questionnaires. Interpretations confirmed by repetitions.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 Had details on 73 families. Convinced Barbara with this. Introduced her to other anthrop
ologists, including Hugh Brody, who impressed her. Barbara got the notes typed. Then sub-classified, 12 photocopies cut up into themes with comments. Fulltime research assistants regrouped material into files, which answered all the questions of the quest
ionnaire. Market researcher employed to put some of the numerical material into computer.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 Visit to Hull, helped by Arthur Ivatts, to see local Gypsies, the only group still horse-drawn \endash  and seen more positively because of that. Farnham Reyfisch, first eth
nographic study of European Gypsies, lived in a tent with Aberdeenshire Gypsies, but his Ph D failed. JO began relationship with Arthur Campbell and through him met Hamish Henderson.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 JO against idea that Scottish tinkers carry remnant of early Scottish Pi
ctish culture. No sense of historical change or relationship to modern life. Scottish Travellers singing ordinary popular songs got drunk.  At Cambridge had been told there were only two types of nomad, hunter-gatherers and pastoralists. JO argued a third
, partially integrated, service nomads. Has been a pioneer in challenging myth of Gypsy Indian origin. Encounter with Hobsbawm, who asked her to write article for }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 
Past and Present}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 , which would have been protective.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\ul\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 Oxford D Phil [1973-6]}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\ul\insrsid8534382 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 Research turned i
nto D. Phil. Difficulty in getting a grant. Malcolm McLeod supported. New professor Maurice Freedman (compromised between Rodney Needham and John Barnes), fearful of student rebels. First registered for B. Litt., for which interviewed by Edwin Ardener. He
 told her that to qualify as a resident she must prominently attend the fortnightly seminar, and go to pub afterwards. Godfrey Leinhardt, supervisor, flexible. Judith living on Gypsy camp.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382 

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 Disappointed that names of chapter authors removed from first book, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 Gypsies and Government Policy
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 . Judith\rquote 
s chapters have been the most quoted. After publication, able to get a small grant from a special trust. Burning of a caravan after a death. Given stolen bag by woman she was helping, which helped JO\rquote s reputation with
 Gypsies, but not with academics. Given pool award for Ph D. No further fieldwork, but kept in touch with contacts.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 Lived first in a room in Headington. Bought a house in Oxford with Jim; then with sale of mother\rquote s house in Acton and Jim\rquote s parents bought 
three storey house in Islington for \'a312,000.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 Peer group - Kirsten Hastrup (now professor in Denmark), Martin Thom, Graham Clark (has died) \endash 
 amazed that JO had already completed her fieldwork. Writing on pollution beliefs, which Barbara Adams thought mumbo jumbo. Days at library were deducted from her annual leave.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 
Godfrey Leinhardt gave no intellectual direction. His student Ahmed al Shahi (Iraqi Kurd) has inherited his papers. Godfrey had Austrian father and English mother, brought up in Yorkshire. Totally supported JO. Alcoholic, as was EP: \lquote 
the Institute was sinking in alcoholism\rquote . All boys pub culture. Rodney Needham and Edwin Ardener didn\rquote t speak, forbad their students to go to the other\rquote s seminars. Bitterness of Philomena Steady, whose supervisor wo
uld not let her write her own way. Godfrey allowed JO to go her way, and she stuck with him.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 Who gave her intellectual inspiration in Oxford? Shirley Ardener ran an all-women seminar, and suggested JO should write her paper on Gypsy women, later published in }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 Perceiving Women}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 .}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382 
