\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\ul\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 Oxford Women\rquote s Anthropology Group and International Gender Studies Centre [from 1970s-present]}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\ul\insrsid8534382 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 Oxford Women\rquote s Anthropology Group evolved from this seminar, started by feminist students in 1972. One pioneers Charlotte Hardma
n (worked in India, now at Durham). Judith joined 1973. Has mentioned in article [in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 Gendered Lessons in Ivory Towers}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 , 2007] on how it was like a women\rquote s conscious-raising group. Not a cockfight, they hoped everyone would speak. Anthropology then very male
 (at Durham all lecturers men). Men would take over seminars without realising. Spoke at Warwick in 2011, \lquote Is Feminism Still Needed/\rquote 
 At Essex started the post-graduate seminar, chaired Edinburgh seminar. Male lecturer who set up students to mock woman speaker. Her own students referred to as \lquote Judith\rquote s eunuchs\rquote .}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f39\fs22\insrsid8534382 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 
Interviews for new book include researchers from Afghanistan, Senegal; some references to former students,  e.g. Clive Foster,  who ran Borstal, did PhD on HIV in Edinburgh. Medical researchers ver
y critical of his qualitative methods, but the HIV users told him, \lquote We want you to tell our story. [JO deliberately did not interview ex-students because wasnted to avoid power relations.] }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f39\fs22\insrsid8534382 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 New intellectual directions from women\rquote s seminar? It was more a space for people to explore ideas in a supportive atmosphere.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f39\fs22\insrsid8534382 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 Still had not finished thesis when got Durham job in 1976. Came back to Oxford 1999. Thursday seminar, but this appears to be threatened by lack of institutional backin
g. Oxford full of highly qualified women who cannot get jobs. From 2001 Deputy Director [of the International Gender Studies Centre, Queen Elizabeth House], but concerned with seminars, not with administration. Sensational seminar series on Mediterranean 
r
un by Lydia Sciama. Another seminar on giving back, with John Parry and Tony Simpson. Hope to switch based on Lady Margaret Hall. JO spoke once at the famous Friday seminar in Oxford. Unusually, showed photos. Wendy James noticed the wreaths on chairs: th
e ghost is settled.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 The all-women\rquote s seminar was not at the Institute of Anthropology because Maurice Freedman objected to the exclusion of men \endash 
 although belonged to All Souls, all-male college. So held instead at Queen Elizabeth House. Also anthropology/I
slamic seminar at Centre for Islamic Studies, led by Mohammed Talib, whom JO has interviewed for book.  She will give seminar on this in November.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\ul\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 Durham [1976-81]}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\ul\insrsid8534382 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 Nine month job, extended twice. Support of David Brooks}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 .}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382  Had to pretend had broken with Jim in order to be taken seriously for the interview for permanent job after two years there.  Objections to appointing her with 3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f39\fs22\super\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 rd}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 , but Durham had appointed a man with no first degree at all. Finally, presented as the firs
t woman President of the Oxford Union. VC: \lquote Gentlemen, this is a very powerful lady\rquote . Married women not shortlisted. Jim by now in and out of mental hospital, but JO never missed a class.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f39\fs22\insrsid8534382 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 Prejudice against studying Europe, because, as Maurice Bloch put it, \lquote We know it\rquote .}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 When came to Essex, welcomed and encouraged by Leonore Davidoff, who gave talk at Durham on feminist history. Anthropologists criticised JO for going to Essex.}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 Not provided with accommodation at Durham. Rented terrace in miners\rquote  village. Retired miners adopted her, excursions, clubs, invited her to their homes \endash 
 escape from college atmosphere. Later when had permanent job bought a terraced house in Durham city.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\ul\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 Essex [1981-90]}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 Already five women on Sociology staff at Essex, but felt not 
welcomed. Stayed six weeks with Gordon Marshall. Boarding school article resonated with Alison Scott, who had been to similar school: became \lquote close buddies\rquote .}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 Taught deviancy with \lquote delightful\rquote  Ken Plummer, from whom learnt about symbolic interactionism. Di
visions within Marxism. Also taught qualitative methods course. Previously, with David Rose, this had been just reading novels. JO\rquote s key texts were W.H. Whyte, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 
Street Corner Society}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 , appendix; Ulf Hannerz}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 ,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\i\f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382  Soul Side}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 , studies of ethnic neighbourhoods, and Michael Agar,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\i\f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382  The Professional Stranger}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 , on  the \lquote funnel method\rquote  \endash 
 start open, then refine. Every researcher she has interviewed has changed focus in the field. JO against hypotheses before fieldwork. Better, to put down \lquote research questions\rquote .  At Essex saw 
the positivist side of methods at work, bullying students with merely six-week projects.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382 
