\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\ul\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 Normandy project [fieldwork 1985-6, with return visits including in 1995] }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\ul\insrsid8534382 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 
Peter Riviere, her internal examiner, invited JO to join ESRC Ageing Initiative. Wanted to just study ageing in France, Normandy, but was asked to make it comparative with Britain \endash  so chose Dedham, Essex [where she lived]. Interesting elderly
 neighbours.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 Again, research direction not predetermined: cf Andr\'e9 Bretoon, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 L\rquote Amour fou. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 Feminist writing on flaneurs: we wander, but open to what comes our way. Hortense Powdermaker, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 
Stranger and Friend}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 , brilliant about fieldwork. Has interviwed 22 anthropologists, cut and pasted hundred of hours of tape.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f39\fs22\insrsid8534382 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 Normandy landings. Paintings by Millet and Impressionists. There was some anthropology of French Mediterranean and Brittany, but little on Normandy. Not remote, \lquote 
the breadbasket or milk and cheese provider of Paris\rquote . Flaubert lived there. So chose an area where she knew the literature but not the people.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 Dropped suggested contact with professor at Caen studying villages. Instead, drove through Normandy with Alan C
ampbell. Found former spa town, Forges les Eaux; in tourist office told they had \lquote too many old people\rquote ! France has high life expectancy. Rented a gite, a converted barn, finishing }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\i\f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 Simone de Beauvoir}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 . Encountered Armistice Day ceremony in church, wreaths an
d band; joined procession to town hall. Through this, met wife of deputy mayor, and explained her purpose, comparison with England, which the mayor promptly announced at reception. Fantastic start to fieldwork.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f39\fs22\insrsid8534382 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 Mitterand giving funds for small clubs. In Forges, these dominated by middle classes. But also some village clubs; here met Jacqueline Gr\'e9
goire, president of one club, small farmer. Informal questions as mode of entry: answering questions while plucking chicken. Finally she shifts to milking, and then teaches JO to hand-milk. Old trick, (learned from Hugh Brody) \lquote Can I help?\rquote 
 Introduced to cow. Took home three-legged stool. Eventually learnt how to milk, while Jacqueline photographed her: \lquote the return of the gaze\rquote . At the end, drank her pure milk. Breakthrough.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f39\fs22\insrsid8534382 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 Changed JO\rquote s ideas on landscape, seen as used space. Never wrote intended monograph on this research. Has written on landscape. Started filming. Fabian had written }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 Time and the Other}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 , arguing that anthropologists have privileged the visual over
 other senses. Film, \lquote Les Enfants du paradis\rquote , Jean-Louis Barraud as clown: \lquote Tout le monde l\rquote a regardee, mais moi j\rquote \'e9tais le seul \'e0 la voir\rquote 
. Similarly Jacqueline sees apple trees which produce cider, grass which produces milk, a worked landscape. Millet\rquote s peasants. Spoke of this in inaugural lecture at Hull. Jacqueline gave her the peasant view of the landscape. John Berger, }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 Ways of Seeing}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 
. But researcher needed more time. Locals wanted to keep variety of apples. Contrasting emptiness of agribusiness landscapes. Filmed landscape, poplars.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 
Dictated fieldnotes onto tape recorder, typed by secretary at Essex. Notes only; no recording directly except at the end of Jacqueline, whom by then knew well. Notes on 60 people in the main club. Knew others in Maisons de Retraite, but they spoke little.
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382\charrsid8534382 
Main effort in Normandy. Some work in Essex, visiting Dedham club, outings and fetes. Had intended complete books on French fieldwork and on methods, but instead published articles. Heavy load of dissertations left over 
from being SOAS external when awarded 1995/6 ESRC Senior Fellowship. Refused to send draft of methods book to ESRC. Present book project started with 4-hour recording of Brian Morris (Goldsmiths) on his fieldwork in India.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 
\ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8534382 
